# Dynamic Range

Adjust dynamic range. Wide dynamic ranges reduce loss of detail in highlights for more natural results with high-contrast or backlit scenes.

| Option | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| AUTO   | Choose for increased contrast. |
| !100% 100% | Reduce loss of detail in highlights. |
| !200% 200% | Reduce loss of detail in highlights. |
| !400% 400% | Reduce loss of detail in highlights. |

> ⚠️ Mottling may appear in pictures taken at higher values. Choose a value according to the scene.

- If **AUTO** is selected, the camera will automatically choose either !100% 100% or !200% 200% according to the subject and shooting conditions. Shutter speed and aperture will be displayed when the shutter button is pressed halfway.
- !200% 200% is available at sensitivities from ISO 160 to ISO 12800.
- !400% 400% at sensitivities from ISO 320 to 12800.
